{% extends 'layouts/base.njk' %}

{% block content %}
<main>
  <section class="intro content">
    <div
      rel="js-headshot"
      class="headshot"
      data-state="original"
      data-tweening="false"
    >
      <img
        alt="Christian Hain's Headshot"
        rel="js-headshot--original"
        src="https://assets.christianhain.com/images/xianhain-headshot.png"
        width="200"
        height="200"
      >
      <img
        alt="Christian's Adobe Creative Type Illustration: The Innovator"
        rel="js-headshot--modified"
        src="https://assets.christianhain.com/images/adobe-innovator.gif"
        class="headshot__modified-img"
        width="200"
        height="200"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
    </div>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
    <p>I'm Christian <span>(he/him)</span>, and I'm an Internet power-user,
      creator, and
      <a
        rel="nofollow"
        href="https://badgecert.com/bc/html/groupbadges.html?k=U1U5Z1BhdlF0Nys4K0VVa2NUOVNMems0cTkybW0yb2Q"
        title="View BadgeCert verified certification"
        target="_blank"
      >Certified Scrum Developer&reg;</a> engineer. Specializing in
      browser-based experiences, my goal is to share what I know about making
      beautiful <abbr title="user interfaces">UI</abbr> and frictionless
      <abbr title="user experiences">UX</abbr> accessible to everyone.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="blog">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-element-bundle.min.js"></script>
    <div class="blog__content">
      <div class="content">
        <h2 class="content__title">This is my blog</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="blog__entries">
        <swiper-container
          rel="js-blog-container"
          grab-cursor="true"
          space-between="16"
          slides-per-view="auto"
          slides-offset-after="16"
          slides-offset-before="16"
          center-insufficient-slides="true"
        >
          {% for item in pagination.items %}
            <swiper-slide class="blog-entry">
              <article>
                <h3 rel="js-blog-entry__title">{{ item.title }}</h3>
                <p rel="js-blog-entry__brief"> {{ item.brief }}</p>
                <p>
                  <a
                    rel="nofollow"
                    href="/blog/{{ item.slug }}"
                    class="cta cta--primary"
                    title="View on Hashnode.com"
                  >
                    Read More
                  </a>
                </p>
              </article>
            </swiper-slide>
          {% endfor %}
        </swiper-container>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="tenants content">
    <h2 id="tenants" class="content__title">These are my tenants</h2>
    <ol aria-labelledby="tenants">
      <li>
        <h3>Premium <abbr title="user interface">UI</abbr> development</h3>
        High-end, accessible interfaces must elevate the user's browsing
        experience. Customers perceive quality based on the standards set by
        their favorite mobile and desktop websites, regardless of industry
        or purpose.
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Maintainable software</h3>
        Yours, mine, oursâ€” everyone is invested in the code. It must be
        logical and maintainable, it must have context about its existence,
        and it must be written cohesively so everyone can understand.
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Full-stack and full-cycle</h3>
        As you know, there's more to a website than its code. In addition to
        business objectives, there's planning, refining, designing,
        prototyping, developing, documenting, testing, deploying,
        supporting, reporting, advertising, marketing, <i>et cetera</i>.
        Therefore, I pay attention to all these aspects to ensure effective
        design and development cycles that favor the investments spent to
        delight the users.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>
  <section class="ctas content">
    <a
      href="https://assets.christianhain.com/pdfs/christian-hain-cv-2022.pdf"
      class="cta cta--primary"
      title="Download PDF"
      target="_blank"
    >
      Download my <abbr title="curriculum vitae">CV</abbr>
    </a>
    <a
      rel="nofollow"
      class="cta cta--primary"
      href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/crhain"
      title="Go to LinkedIn.com"
      target="_blank"
    >
      Check out my LinkedIn
    </a>
  </section>
</main>

{% endblock %}